sentence: Weyerhaeuser CompanyWY is scheduled to report fourth-quarter 2015 results on Feb 5 before the market opens.
The Zacks Consensus Estimate for the quarter is pegged at 24 cents per share.
The company delivered lower-than-expected results in two out of the four trailing quarters, while faring impressively in the rest.
Average earnings surprise for the stock is a positive 6.61%.
Last quarter, Weyerhaeuser's earnings of 35 cents per share had surpassed the Zacks Consensus Estimate of 27 cents.
Let us see how things are shaping up prior to this announcement.
Weyerhaeuser is globally recognized for its forest products.
We believe the company is well-positioned to reap benefits from its cost-control measures and a gradual recovery in the U.S. housing market.

However, Weyerhaeuser's timberland and wood products businesses are directly influenced by the housing market in the U.S. Also, the company's international operations expose it to risks arising from unfavorable foreign currency movements and geopolitical issues.
Any economic unrest in the foreign countries served by the company will negatively affect its businesses.
At the same time, the company encounters threats from stiff competition and high debt levels.
For fourth-quarter 2015, Weyerhaeuser anticipates sequentially comparable earnings from its Timberlands segment, while predicting lower earnings for the Cellulose Fibers and Wood Products segments.
Our proven model conclusively shows that Weyerhaeuser will lag earnings this quarter.
That is because a stock needs to have both a positive Earnings ESP and a Zacks Rank #1 (Strong Buy), 2 (Buy) or 3 (Hold) for a likely earnings beat.
That is not the case here as you will see below.
Zacks ESP: Weyerhaeuser currently has an ESP of -4.17% for fourth-quarter 2015.
This is because the Most Accurate Estimate of 23 cents stands lower than the Zacks Consensus Estimate of 24 cents.

Here are companies in the building products industry you may want to consider, as our model shows they have the right combination of elements to post an earnings beat this quarter:

Lowe's Companies, Inc. LOW , with an Earnings ESP of +6.78% and a Zacks Rank #2.
Louisiana-Pacific Corp. LPX , with an Earnings ESP of +33.33% and a Zacks Rank #2.
The Home Depot, Inc. HD , with an Earnings ESP of +0.91% and a Zacks Rank #3.
